The endocrine system plays a major role in the regulation of several biological 
activity and in the ageing process. Evolutionary conservation of 
GH/IGF-I/insulin pathway from worms to mice and similarities in this system 
between mice and humans raised expectations that downregulated activity of the 
GH/IGF-I/insulin pathway could be beneficial for the extension of human life 
